import cacheable from 'cacheable';
function cachedMyComponent(props) {

 return (
     <div>
         {(cachedProps && cachedState.props !== undefined)
             ? (<MyObject {...(cachedProp as any)} />)
                 : ({...props})
            }
      </div>

 );
}

return(
<CacheProvider value={cachable(MyComponent)}>
{(<App />)}
</CacheProviders>  
);
```
This approach helps reduce unnecessary computations on each component load while maintaining responsiveness.

3. Utilize optimized libraries & frameworks: Selecting suitable JavaScript modules such as Three.js library is crucial here - it provides powerful functions for working with three-dimensional geometry models efficiently.
4. Reduce redundant calculations within loops/for-loops over massive datasets via parallel processing capabilities offered through CPU/GPU acceleration provided by modern CPUs/CUDA devices / GPUs.
5. Consider implementing algorithms specifically designed for optimizing high-performance graphics-intensive tasks common associated with game development e.g.: Bresenham's line algorithm for drawing lines based upon their coordinates; Fast Marching Technique used for smoothing out noise inside polygons).
6. Leverage browser-based optimizations whenever possible since web browsers tend not favor expensive computational operations compared to native implementations running directly under NodeJS environments where server-side computation might dominate execution times). 

